{"name": "flet-contrib", "metadata": {"name": "flet-contrib", "version": "2024.3.6", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "", "license": "Apache-2.0", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["flet-core"], "summary": "Flet controls by the community", "upload_time": 1709756039}, "documentation": ["# Flet controls in Python by the community\n\n`flet-contrib` package includes reusable Flet controls written in Python only and using existing Flet primitives.\n\n## Controls\n\n* [ColorPicker](flet_contrib/color_picker) ([Live demo](https://flet-controls-gallery.fly.dev/contrib/colorpicker))\n\n## Usage\n\nTo install `flet-contrib` package:\n\n```\npip install flet-contrib\n```\n\nTo use in your app:\n\n```python\nfrom flet_contrib.color_picker import ColorPicker\n\npicker = ColorPicker(...)\n```\n\n## How to contribute\n\nContributions are welcome!\n\nFork this repo.\n\nCreate a new directory inside `flet_contrib` for your control(s) - that will be control's module name, for example `flet_contrib.my_control`.\n\nControl directory structure:\n\n* `README.md` - control description, usage, examples, support information.\n* `/src` - control implementation.\n* `/media` - images, multimedia files, databases and other files required by control to function or used in `README.md`.\n* `/examples` - one or more examples of usage of your control.\n* `__init__.py` - classes and functions exported to users of your control.\n\nSee [ColorPicker](flet_contrib/color_picker) for folder structure example.\n\nSubmit Pull Request (PR) with your changes.\n\nOnce your PR is merged into `main` a new \"dev\" package will be released [here](https://pypi.org/project/flet-contrib/) which can be installed with `pip install flet-contrib --pre`.\n\nWhen the contribution is tested by Flet team/community a new `flet-contrib` release will be published.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "flet_contrib.audio_player", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "flet_contrib.audio_player.AudioPlayer", "xref": {"fqname": "flet_contrib.audio_player.src.audio_player.AudioPlayer", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "flet_contrib.audio_player.src.utils", "documentation": ["request this only when you have done timedelta(milliseconds=...)"], "functions": [{"name": "flet_contrib.audio_player.src.utils.format_timedelta_str_ms", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "timedelta_milliseconds_str", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Examples:\nformat_timedelta_str(\"0:00:40.399000\") -> \"00:40\"\nformat_timedelta_str(\"0:00:40.600000\") -> \"00:41\""]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "flet_contrib.audio_player.examples.audio_player_example", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "flet_contrib.audio_player.examples.audio_player_example.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "page", "type": {"name": "ft.Page", "xref": {"fqname": "flet.Page", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "flet_contrib.flexible_slider.examples.horizontal_slider_example", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "flet_contrib.flexible_slider.examples.horizontal_slider_example.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "page", "type": {"name": "ft.Page", "xref": {"fqname": "flet.Page", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "flet_contrib.flexible_slider", "documentation": [], "functions": [],